WEBVTT

00:03.870 --> 00:06.031
- Good morning, Sabrina.
- Hi, there.

00:07.640 --> 00:08.800
Bye there. I'm off to work.

00:08.975 --> 00:10.033
You're late for work again?

00:10.210 --> 00:11.905
You better be careful
or you'll get sick.

00:12.078 --> 00:13.705
And for goodness sakes,
put on a jacket.

00:15.248 --> 00:18.240
And be sure to call and give us
an idea of when you'll be home,

00:18.418 --> 00:20.511
otherwise, I'll just sit up and worry.

00:20.687 --> 00:22.780
Isn't that neckline a little low,
young lady?

00:25.091 --> 00:27.423
Guys, I appreciate your concern,
but I'm a grown-up.

00:27.594 --> 00:28.891
I can take care of myself.

00:29.062 --> 00:30.586
Fine, but it really is cold out there.

00:30.763 --> 00:32.162
I can handle it.

00:33.466 --> 00:35.798
Holy cheese and crackers.
Cold, cold, cold.

00:36.269 --> 00:39.067
Now, do you wanna come in
and get your coat?

00:40.340 --> 00:42.808
I said I could handle it.

00:42.976 --> 00:46.468
Oh, great,
how am I supposed to get my keys?

00:48.000 --> 00:54.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:22.385 --> 01:23.511
[GRUNTS]

01:23.686 --> 01:27.383
My neck is stiffer than my writing.

01:27.557 --> 01:29.252
This is bad.

01:29.425 --> 01:30.449
[SIGHS]

01:30.626 --> 01:33.424
<i>I've been working around the clock,</i>
<i>help me shake this writer's block.</i>

01:34.197 --> 01:35.255
Whew!

01:35.431 --> 01:39.891
Not what I was going for,
but, uh, this is nice too.

01:40.336 --> 01:41.735
[CLEARS THROAT]

01:41.904 --> 01:43.337
Oops.

01:43.506 --> 01:45.303
How long have you
been standing there?

01:45.742 --> 01:50.179
Long enough to realize
that you are a very beautiful woman.

01:51.347 --> 01:52.678
That was forward of me. I'm sorry.

01:52.849 --> 01:55.818
Oh, no, no, no. Don't be sorry.
Be, um, continuing. Heh.

01:55.985 --> 01:57.612
- I'm Victor.
- Sabrina.

01:57.787 --> 01:59.084
Yeah, I just bought this chair

01:59.255 --> 02:02.383
because I'm, uh, researching
a story about loafing.

02:02.558 --> 02:03.957
So are you a freelancer?

02:04.127 --> 02:05.151
I own a record label,

02:05.328 --> 02:07.523
and I was just dropping off
some promotional material.

02:07.697 --> 02:09.358
Oh, well,
then we have something in common.

02:09.532 --> 02:11.796
You own a record label,
and I own a label maker.

02:11.968 --> 02:14.801
This is totally out of the blue,
but, um, do you have plans tonight?

02:15.238 --> 02:18.537
Not really,
except for writing and vibrating.

02:18.708 --> 02:22.007
I own this gallery,
and we're having an opening tonight.

02:22.178 --> 02:23.645
Would you like to join me?

02:23.813 --> 02:26.008
I was supposed to go for seafood
with my roommates.

02:26.182 --> 02:28.514
I hear there's gonna be
really good food.

02:29.018 --> 02:31.816
Let's see, going to a gallery opening
with a handsome single guy,

02:31.988 --> 02:34.513
or fighting with Roxie
over a tiny bag of oyster crackers?

02:34.690 --> 02:36.783
- I'll buy you a sculpture.
- Sold. Ha, ha.

02:37.160 --> 02:38.388
Hey, Harv, what brings you by?

02:38.561 --> 02:40.153
Oh, nothing special.

02:40.329 --> 02:43.560
You know, I haven't seen you
in a while, and I miss you.

02:43.733 --> 02:46.566
- What do you want to watch?
- Canadian celebrity hockey.

02:46.736 --> 02:48.727
I'm gonna get cable
one of these days, I swear.

02:48.905 --> 02:50.634
Well, watch away.
I'm not even gonna be here.

02:50.807 --> 02:53.833
But I am. <i>Dr. Dolittle's</i> on tonight.

02:54.277 --> 02:57.269
Something about a talking animal
just cracks me up.

02:57.447 --> 02:59.608
Oh, no. It looks like
I'm getting crows feet right here.

02:59.782 --> 03:01.044
[CAWING]

03:01.217 --> 03:02.479
Oops.

03:02.652 --> 03:05.052
- Why did that happen?
- Who knows?

03:05.221 --> 03:07.553
Do I have to explain everything?

03:07.723 --> 03:10.021
Ever since you've been on this
"I'm a grown-up" kick,

03:10.193 --> 03:11.592
you've hardly used your magic.

03:11.761 --> 03:13.752
It's pent up and it's gonna come out.

03:13.930 --> 03:15.659
You know,
I've been doing fine without magic.

03:15.832 --> 03:16.924
Maybe I'll just give it up.

03:17.100 --> 03:18.124
Wait a minute.

03:18.301 --> 03:21.236
How are you gonna quit magic?
Go to Witch Watchers?

03:21.404 --> 03:24.100
No, I'll just store it in this container.

03:24.273 --> 03:26.571
I can't believe
you'd give up your magic.

03:26.742 --> 03:28.004
It's so much a part of you.

03:28.177 --> 03:29.804
Well, I don't really need it anymore.

03:29.979 --> 03:31.571
And lately, every time I try to use it,

03:31.747 --> 03:33.908
like tonight at the office,
I almost get busted.

03:35.485 --> 03:36.782
Are you sure that will hold it?

03:36.953 --> 03:39.080
Yeah, Tupperware
is the only thing that can hold magic.

03:39.255 --> 03:41.883
They say Houdini died
of locked-in freshness.

03:42.058 --> 03:44.891
There. Good to the last drop.

03:45.061 --> 03:47.791
I know what you're thinking.
I don't want you anywhere near this.

03:47.964 --> 03:50.558
Oh, come on. Just a little?

03:50.733 --> 03:52.667
I don't wanna be a cat anymore.

03:53.035 --> 03:54.662
Harvey, you hold on to it.

03:55.872 --> 03:56.930
Wow.

03:57.106 --> 03:58.334
It doesn't want to leave you.

03:58.508 --> 04:02.274
Aw, my magic goo
has separation anxiety.

04:05.248 --> 04:07.216
Come on, Salem,
we'll have a great time.

04:07.383 --> 04:09.351
We've got soda, we've got popcorn,

04:09.519 --> 04:13.512
and we've got four hours of Canada's
brightest TV stars playing hockey.

04:14.157 --> 04:16.057
Hey, Harvey,
want to come to dinner with us?

04:16.225 --> 04:17.624
It's this really fun seafood place.

04:17.793 --> 04:19.851
The bathrooms
are for wenches and mateys.

04:20.296 --> 04:21.320
That sounds cool.

04:21.497 --> 04:22.521
[GASPS]

04:22.698 --> 04:25.633
Alan Thicke is about to sing
"O, Canada."

04:25.801 --> 04:27.769
You guys go ahead.

04:27.937 --> 04:30.167
Actually, um,
there's been a change of plans.

04:30.339 --> 04:31.363
See, I met this guy,

04:31.541 --> 04:34.533
and he told me about an opening
in an art gallery with music and food...

04:34.710 --> 04:36.007
- Oh.
- We get what you're saying.

04:36.179 --> 04:37.646
Good. I didn't wanna disappoint you.

04:37.813 --> 04:40.111
Oh, don't worry.
We can go to dinner any old time.

04:40.283 --> 04:42.751
- We'll be ready to go in two minutes.
- Guys.

04:42.919 --> 04:44.147
Sabrina, it's okay.

04:44.320 --> 04:47.312
We know how awkward it is to go to a
party where you don't know anybody.

04:47.490 --> 04:49.117
That's what we're here for.

04:49.292 --> 04:50.316
And don't worry,

04:50.493 --> 04:53.326
I won't wear my best stuff,
so you'll still look pretty.

04:54.230 --> 04:56.824
Sometimes, I swear, they are two
of the most dense people I know.

04:56.999 --> 04:58.091
[SIGHS]

04:58.267 --> 05:01.327
I wonder if we'll ever have
a Canadian president?

05:02.605 --> 05:04.505
Maybe there's a gas leak
in this house.

05:07.109 --> 05:08.736
I gotta say, this great gallery opening

05:08.911 --> 05:11.243
you wanted us to come to
kind of sucks.

05:11.414 --> 05:15.783
Yeah, and next time, do us a favor,
don't drag us to your artsy-fartsy party.

05:15.952 --> 05:17.510
Okay, well, if this isn't your thing,

05:17.687 --> 05:19.552
you still have time
to go to dinner without me.

05:19.722 --> 05:20.746
[SIGHS]

05:20.923 --> 05:23.619
No, I mean, we're here,
and I did my hair,

05:23.793 --> 05:25.784
and Roxie put on deodorant.

05:25.962 --> 05:27.896
Since we're stuck here
amongst these losers,

05:28.064 --> 05:30.328
we should come up
with a safe word.

05:30.499 --> 05:31.523
Safe word?

05:31.701 --> 05:33.566
Code word,
in case we get cornered by some geek.

05:33.736 --> 05:35.363
Or someone poor.

05:35.538 --> 05:37.529
Okay, how about zoo?

05:37.707 --> 05:39.572
Sabrina,
the whole point of a safe word,

05:39.742 --> 05:42.142
is that it wouldn't come up
in normal conversation.

05:42.712 --> 05:44.009
Zoo won't work.

05:44.180 --> 05:45.477
"Oh, this place is a zoo."

05:45.648 --> 05:47.275
"What a zoo it is in here."

05:47.450 --> 05:49.941
"Sure, I'll make out
in the monkey house at the zoo."

05:50.119 --> 05:52.519
Okay, kazoo. How's that?

05:52.688 --> 05:54.212
Fine, kazoo.

05:54.390 --> 05:55.414
Come on, Roxie,

05:55.591 --> 05:57.354
I'll teach you
how to pick up a cater waiter.

06:00.896 --> 06:03.490
So, what do you think of the gallery?

06:03.666 --> 06:07.864
Oh, I like this, uh, tangled
chrome thingy.

06:08.037 --> 06:10.028
It's too bad
somebody left their orange in it.

06:10.206 --> 06:12.003
I think that's part of sculpture.

06:12.174 --> 06:15.234
Oh, in that case, I may have
just eaten a $6,000 banana.

06:17.680 --> 06:20.706
Come on, buddy, pal, <i>compadre.</i>

06:20.883 --> 06:23.977
How about sharing a little
of Sabrina's mojo with me?

06:24.153 --> 06:26.621
Salem, Sabrina said no.

06:26.789 --> 06:29.349
And I dated her. No means no.

06:29.525 --> 06:30.549
Fine.

06:30.993 --> 06:34.827
But if I had that magic, I could
turn you into a Canadian celebrity,

06:34.997 --> 06:36.658
and you could be out there
on that ice

06:36.832 --> 06:40.359
having your teeth
knocked out by k.d. Lang.

06:41.771 --> 06:43.932
- No.
- Unh!

06:45.574 --> 06:46.871
This is much better, huh?

06:47.043 --> 06:48.510
Much.

06:48.978 --> 06:52.880
Yeah, this certainly is the most
comfortable piece of art I ever sat on.

06:53.049 --> 06:54.812
So, uh, do you choose
all the pieces yourself?

06:54.984 --> 06:57.384
Oh, no, no.
The gallery is just a side business.

06:57.553 --> 07:00.386
My personal collection
tends to be more eclectic.

07:00.556 --> 07:02.922
Mine too.
I have 20 of the 50 state quarters.

07:03.092 --> 07:05.560
Impressive.
Listen, let's get out of here.

07:05.728 --> 07:07.958
I mean, why don't you come
to my home for an after party.

07:08.130 --> 07:10.325
And I'm gonna have a live band
and really cool people,

07:10.499 --> 07:13.662
and I promise,
it'll be much better than this.

07:13.836 --> 07:15.133
Well, okay.

07:15.304 --> 07:17.238
I mean, after all,
I've already eaten all the art.

07:17.740 --> 07:20.300
- I need to tell somebody I'm leaving.
- Okay.

07:21.777 --> 07:23.677
- Hey, guys, listen, l...
- Kazoo.

07:23.846 --> 07:26.337
Oh, don't you feel terrible
for that poor supermodel outside?

07:26.515 --> 07:29.279
The way both of her straps
just snapped off like that?

07:29.852 --> 07:31.046
Thank you.

07:31.220 --> 07:33.450
Listen, Victor's having an after party
at his house, so...

07:33.622 --> 07:35.453
I can't go.
I have to get to the radio show.

07:35.624 --> 07:38.593
That's okay. I'll bring back as much
food as I can stuff in my pockets.

07:38.761 --> 07:40.228
Hello? Larry? Curly?

07:40.396 --> 07:42.364
You're not invited.
Can't you guys take a hint?

07:42.898 --> 07:44.388
Whoa.

07:44.567 --> 07:47.866
And whoa... is me too.

07:48.037 --> 07:50.164
So you're going alone to a party
at this guy's house?

07:50.339 --> 07:52.398
- You don't even know him.
MORGAN: Roxie's right.

07:52.575 --> 07:55.135
You need someone to come along
and watch your back.

07:55.311 --> 07:56.744
It's called the buddy system.

07:56.912 --> 07:58.743
I don't need a buddy,
I don't need a chaperone,

07:58.914 --> 08:00.609
and I don't need you
acting like my aunts.

08:00.783 --> 08:03.013
I'm an adult.
I can take care of myself.

08:03.185 --> 08:04.675
- Ready?
- Yeah.

08:04.854 --> 08:06.412
- Look, I'm sorry.
- Okay, whatever.

08:06.589 --> 08:08.921
Have fun. Come on, Morgan.

08:09.091 --> 08:10.524
Well...

08:11.127 --> 08:14.585
You have lipstick on your teeth,
and I'm not going to tell you.

08:16.332 --> 08:17.560
Is everything all right?

08:17.733 --> 08:20.725
Oh, yeah, you know,
nothing an arm can't take care of.

08:23.339 --> 08:26.069
All this
just so I can thumb wrestle again.

08:26.242 --> 08:29.439
Okay, let's make magic.

08:32.448 --> 08:33.847
[SCREAMS]

08:37.253 --> 08:39.813
Oh, there's no stopping genius.

08:39.989 --> 08:41.581
[GROANS]

08:41.924 --> 08:42.948
[WHIMPERS]

08:52.800 --> 08:55.200
What an amazing house.

08:55.400 --> 08:56.800
Is that the Goo Goo Dolls?

08:57.500 --> 08:59.500
Yeah, they're my friends.

09:42.000 --> 09:44.000
We'll take a little break
and we'll be right back.

09:44.200 --> 09:49.260
I can't believe you have the Goo Goo Dolls here.
Morgan Loves the Goo Goo Dolls, I should call her.

09:49.460 --> 09:51.792
You are everything
that I have been looking for.

09:53.097 --> 09:55.395
On second thought,
she can just buy herself the CD.

09:55.566 --> 09:57.033
So, who's performing
here tomorrow?

09:57.201 --> 09:58.225
The Three Tenors.

09:58.402 --> 10:01.633
Oh, remind me, I have to stock
the pantry full of luncheon meats.

10:06.577 --> 10:09.068
Mr. Victor, I must congratulate you.

10:09.246 --> 10:11.806
It is the rarest collection
I've seen yet.

10:11.982 --> 10:13.779
Well, perhaps we can do business.

10:13.951 --> 10:15.441
Let me walk you out.

10:15.619 --> 10:17.382
Sabrina, please excuse me.

10:17.555 --> 10:19.079
No problem.

10:21.559 --> 10:22.685
Excuse me.

10:22.860 --> 10:23.884
Pardon.

10:24.061 --> 10:26.825
Sorry, not cutting in,
just cutting through.

10:30.935 --> 10:32.527
Right, no magic.

10:32.703 --> 10:34.534
Well, I guess
I'll have to do this with smarts,

10:34.705 --> 10:37.572
with know-how, with redial.

10:39.343 --> 10:41.777
Gotta love today's technology.

10:50.854 --> 10:52.515
Whoa.

10:53.356 --> 10:54.380
[GROWLING]

10:54.558 --> 10:55.855
Oh, my...

10:59.096 --> 11:00.120
[GASPS]

11:00.297 --> 11:02.026
Kazoo.

11:02.068 --> 11:04.798
He wants to cage me?

11:04.971 --> 11:06.802
MAN:
Oh, boy, we got a bright one.

11:08.909 --> 11:10.740
Are you a real leprechaun?

11:10.911 --> 11:12.811
Heck, no,
I'm just some short Irish guy

11:12.979 --> 11:15.573
who happened to be caught
drinking a Shamrock Shake.

11:15.749 --> 11:17.444
Well, is everyone else
in here a fake?

11:17.884 --> 11:20.011
Well, I believe
the mermaid has implants,

11:20.187 --> 11:21.779
but I know Bigfoot's real.

11:22.689 --> 11:25.522
The only thing
Victor feeds him is campers.

11:27.060 --> 11:29.426
Well, when Victor said he was
a collector, I had no idea.

11:29.596 --> 11:31.689
I'm gonna free all of you. I swear.

11:31.865 --> 11:34.800
But first I have to deal
with this sicko.

11:36.536 --> 11:39.334
I can't believe
he has all 50 quarters.

11:39.673 --> 11:41.971
"Reversing
a human-to-cat spell."

11:42.142 --> 11:48.240
<i>Make me human, make me whole,</i>
<i>I'm sick of eating from a bowl.</i>

11:49.049 --> 11:50.573
[GASPS]

11:50.750 --> 11:55.210
Ugh. Now the litter sand
is gonna get stuck between my toes.

11:58.291 --> 12:01.124
- There you are.
- Hey, where's everyone going?

12:01.294 --> 12:03.319
Well, everyone left.
You know, which is good, right?

12:03.496 --> 12:06.021
Because that means
you and I can be alone.

12:06.199 --> 12:07.223
Yeah, that's great.

12:07.400 --> 12:09.061
But, um, I'm feeling a little peckish.

12:09.236 --> 12:12.034
I don't suppose you have any crackers,
or a cheeseburger would be great.

12:12.205 --> 12:14.765
- If it's not too much trouble, a soufflé.
- I'll see what I have.

12:14.941 --> 12:17.637
- The Goo Goo Dolls left some sushi.
- Oh, I like my sushi well done.

12:22.349 --> 12:24.408
We're talking about girls
who ditch their girlfriends

12:24.584 --> 12:26.950
as soon as a guy comes along.

12:27.120 --> 12:28.587
You're on the air. Were you ditched?

12:28.755 --> 12:30.518
SABRINA [OVER PHONE]:
<i>Roxie, it's me, Sabrina.</i>

12:30.690 --> 12:32.658
Oh, it's not the ditchee.
It's the ditcher.

12:32.826 --> 12:33.986
<i>I need your help.</i>

12:34.160 --> 12:36.025
Of course you do, now!

12:36.196 --> 12:37.788
Seriously, Rox. This guy's nuts.

12:37.964 --> 12:42.298
Who, Mr. Cashmere-Sock-Wearing
Art-Gallery-After-Party-Thrower?

12:42.469 --> 12:45.097
Well, I didn't learn his last name,
but it can't be that long.

12:45.272 --> 12:47.263
He wants to add me
to his gruesome collection.

12:47.440 --> 12:48.702
That's right.

12:48.875 --> 12:51.571
Put down the other girls
if it makes you feel better.

12:51.745 --> 12:53.269
Let's take another call.

12:53.446 --> 12:55.914
No, Roxie, don't hang up on me.

12:58.184 --> 13:01.210
[PHONE RINGING]

13:01.655 --> 13:03.816
Harvey, the phone.

13:04.457 --> 13:06.448
What the heck is this?

13:06.626 --> 13:11.154
Oh, uh, I was just making
some homemade jam.

13:11.331 --> 13:13.595
Zucchini jam.

13:14.668 --> 13:16.499
- Hello?
- Morgan, it's me.

13:16.670 --> 13:20.265
Oh, well,
if it isn't Susie-Snooty-Society-Snob.

13:20.440 --> 13:21.498
This is important.

13:21.675 --> 13:24.166
Tell Harvey to come
to Victor's party with the Tupperware.

13:24.344 --> 13:25.641
It's a Tupperware party?

13:25.812 --> 13:27.507
Just tell him.
He'll know what I mean.

13:27.681 --> 13:31.742
Victor is extremely handsome
and hygienic.

13:31.918 --> 13:33.579
And he lives in that big house
on Post Road

13:33.753 --> 13:35.277
with the fountain
full of peeing angels.

13:35.455 --> 13:38.049
- Who is that?
- Oh, my, uh, answering machine.

13:38.224 --> 13:40.055
Kazoo, kazoo.

13:40.226 --> 13:41.420
I was just saying hi to my cat.

13:41.962 --> 13:43.589
Kazoo's a weird name for a cat.

13:43.763 --> 13:46.459
Oh, then you don't want to know
about her sister, Fluegelhorn.

13:46.633 --> 13:48.897
This has been really great,
but I really should get going.

13:49.069 --> 13:50.866
Oh, no,
that's not gonna work for me.

13:51.037 --> 13:53.005
You know what they say,
the guest is always right.

13:53.173 --> 13:55.368
- It's the customer.
- Actually, I think it's the guest.

13:55.542 --> 13:58.477
Um, why don't we look it up, compare
notes tomorrow over the phone.

13:58.645 --> 14:02.581
You know, I have been
searching everywhere for a witch.

14:02.749 --> 14:05.343
India, Guam, Wichita.

14:05.518 --> 14:07.213
And that seemed like a sure thing.

14:07.387 --> 14:09.947
And then, poof,
you suddenly appear.

14:10.123 --> 14:11.420
Witch? You think I'm a witch?

14:11.591 --> 14:13.991
Sometimes when someone gets
in the express line with 11 items,

14:14.160 --> 14:15.252
I get a little cranky, but...

14:15.428 --> 14:18.295
If you're not, then how did you make
that massage chair magically appear?

14:18.465 --> 14:20.797
I saw a guy on TV
make the Statue of Liberty disappear,

14:20.967 --> 14:22.525
I mean, ugh,
how do you explain that?

14:22.702 --> 14:23.896
- Let's go.
- Victor, get real.

14:24.070 --> 14:26.300
If I don't come home,
my friends will be here to save me.

14:26.473 --> 14:29.237
Your friends? You mean the two girls
that you ditched at the gallery?

14:30.176 --> 14:32.406
It hardly seemed
like they were your friends.

14:35.548 --> 14:37.607
- Score.
MAN [ON TV]: <i>What a shot...</i>

14:37.784 --> 14:39.775
I just don't understand.

14:39.953 --> 14:42.751
Well, hockey is
a very complicated game.

14:43.323 --> 14:46.053
No, why are they
showing this on TV?

14:49.729 --> 14:52.721
- Hey, Rox. Are you okay?
- I don't know.

14:52.899 --> 14:55.561
Sabrina called me at the radio station,
and I blew her off.

14:55.735 --> 14:57.202
I think she might
have wanted to talk.

14:57.570 --> 14:59.037
Oh, she couldn't have
been too upset.

14:59.205 --> 15:02.641
She called here to ask Harvey to bring
some Tupperware to Victor's party.

15:02.809 --> 15:04.743
- That's a rave.
- What?

15:04.911 --> 15:06.105
How did she sound?

15:06.279 --> 15:08.804
Sick. Sneezing all over the place.

15:08.982 --> 15:10.609
Kachoo. Kachoo.

15:10.784 --> 15:12.445
Are you sure it wasn't kazoo?

15:12.619 --> 15:15.110
Why would someone
sneezing say?

15:16.322 --> 15:17.687
Oopsie.

15:17.857 --> 15:19.620
She was calling for help,
and we ignored her.

15:19.793 --> 15:22.762
Sabrina's in trouble.
I'll get the Tupperware.

15:25.131 --> 15:26.257
[SMACKING LIPS]

15:26.433 --> 15:28.799
I'd forgotten how good this feels.

15:31.337 --> 15:32.770
Salem, what happened?

15:32.939 --> 15:36.306
These little piggies
went to the freak show.

15:36.910 --> 15:37.934
Help me, Harvey.

15:38.111 --> 15:42.741
Okay, here's some magic.

15:43.850 --> 15:46.478
Do something about that foot.
It's disgusting.

15:50.290 --> 15:53.259
I have to admit, it is unsightly.

15:53.426 --> 15:58.420
<i>Magic spell gone kaput,</i>
<i>help me fix this ugly foot.</i>

15:59.365 --> 16:01.890
Hmm. That's better.

16:02.068 --> 16:03.092
You're making a mistake.

16:03.269 --> 16:05.760
If I was a witch, I'd be able
to magically cast a spell and...

16:05.939 --> 16:06.963
Silence!

16:07.140 --> 16:08.334
[DOORBELL CHIMES]

16:08.508 --> 16:10.772
Oh, pizza's here.

16:11.578 --> 16:13.170
Don't forget about the crazy bread.

16:13.346 --> 16:17.180
Yeah, well, I think he's already had
a few loaves of that already.

16:17.684 --> 16:19.015
This is all my fault.

16:19.185 --> 16:20.743
My friends tried to warn me.

16:20.920 --> 16:22.649
All they were doing
was trying to protect me,

16:22.822 --> 16:24.585
and all I did
was treat them like dirt.

16:24.757 --> 16:27.988
If I didn't have friends, I wouldn't be
able to sneak on the rides at Six Flags.

16:33.133 --> 16:34.725
Is Sabrina here?

16:34.901 --> 16:37.267
No, I think she left
with a Goo Goo Doll.

16:37.437 --> 16:40.201
There were party favors?

16:40.940 --> 16:43.534
It sounds like there is more than
just one pizza boy up there.

16:43.710 --> 16:44.938
Maybe it's my friends.

16:45.111 --> 16:46.669
Okay, I gotta think.

16:46.846 --> 16:48.370
I gotta come up with a plan.

16:48.548 --> 16:50.948
I gotta find out what kind
of conditioner that mermaid uses.

16:53.987 --> 16:55.955
See, everyone's gone.

16:56.122 --> 16:58.249
Oh, yeah, well, I think you're lying.

16:59.225 --> 17:00.852
Come on, you guys, let's go.
I hate liars.

17:01.661 --> 17:02.685
[SASQUATCH GROWLS]

17:02.862 --> 17:05.228
- What was that?
- It must have been the pipes.

17:05.397 --> 17:06.422
[SASQUATCH GROWLS]

17:06.598 --> 17:08.499
- And that?
- Oh, no, I just remembered.

17:08.667 --> 17:10.932
My Moroccan friend
is getting a bikini wax.

17:12.704 --> 17:14.695
[GROWLING]

17:22.182 --> 17:25.913
Victor, you like art, right?

17:26.085 --> 17:29.885
You know, a lot of people tell me
that I remind them of that painting,

17:30.056 --> 17:31.614
<i>Venus on a Half Shell.</i>

17:31.791 --> 17:32.849
What do you think?

17:33.026 --> 17:35.586
Venus? Yeah, maybe.

17:35.962 --> 17:38.692
Well, you have to imagine me
without my clothes.

17:38.865 --> 17:41.231
- I'll try.
- I've gotta give her props.

17:41.401 --> 17:43.096
She's a very accomplished tart.

17:43.269 --> 17:44.668
Go.

17:45.605 --> 17:47.334
Sabrina?

17:47.807 --> 17:50.469
All right,
now undress me with your eyes.

17:51.611 --> 17:53.579
No, the zipper's in the back.

17:53.980 --> 17:55.675
Sabrina?

18:03.189 --> 18:05.282
She must be in there.

18:23.509 --> 18:26.603
And I'm the one
with the drinking problem.

18:26.779 --> 18:27.803
Ew.

18:27.981 --> 18:30.347
Oh, that's right. It's diet goo.

18:31.150 --> 18:33.084
Sabrina, are you okay?

18:33.253 --> 18:35.084
I'm fine.

18:35.521 --> 18:36.852
Oh, thanks, Harvey.

18:37.023 --> 18:38.047
[SASQUATCH GROWLING]

18:38.224 --> 18:39.691
Oh, my God, it's so big and hairy.

18:39.859 --> 18:41.451
Oh, don't worry, Harvey,
it's in a cage.

18:41.628 --> 18:43.619
No, there's a spider.

18:43.796 --> 18:46.060
Oh, come on, Harvey,
let's blow this joint.

18:46.766 --> 18:47.790
Going somewhere?

18:47.967 --> 18:50.765
I know you're all grown up now and
you don't wanna use your magic, but...

18:50.937 --> 18:52.871
Yeah, whatever.

18:54.807 --> 18:57.867
Look, Harvey,
I've learned something tonight.

18:58.044 --> 19:00.535
There are two things I'm lucky to have:
My friends and my magic.

19:00.713 --> 19:02.977
And I wouldn't give them up
for anything.

19:03.149 --> 19:04.707
I should have stuck with stamps.

19:05.752 --> 19:07.276
My work here is done.

19:07.453 --> 19:09.148
Wait, what about us?

19:09.756 --> 19:12.156
Oh, sorry. I completely forgot.

19:12.325 --> 19:14.350
<i>Uh, Mermaid, Sasquatch,</i>
<i>back to your homes.</i>

19:17.030 --> 19:18.930
So, Angus,
where would you like to go?

19:19.098 --> 19:21.293
Well, I got a wife and 12 kids
back in Ireland.

19:21.668 --> 19:22.726
Ireland it is.

19:22.902 --> 19:25.200
Wait, are you nuts?
Send me to Vegas.

19:25.371 --> 19:26.429
Ireland it is.

19:26.606 --> 19:29.336
[IN IRISH ACCENT]
Give thee some of my pot of gold.

19:29.509 --> 19:31.238
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Worth a shot.

19:32.478 --> 19:34.002
Let's go.

19:37.717 --> 19:38.775
[IN UNISON]
Sabrina.

19:38.951 --> 19:42.318
Roxie, Morgan.
I am so, so, so, so sorry.

19:42.488 --> 19:45.048
I took you both for granted,
I was a lousy friend,

19:45.224 --> 19:47.692
and I borrowed your clothes
without telling you.

19:47.860 --> 19:50.260
Wait, that wasn't part of it,
but I'm really sorry about that.

19:50.430 --> 19:52.455
Sabrina, it's okay. We forgive you.

19:52.632 --> 19:54.259
We just wanted you
to be happy and safe.

19:54.434 --> 19:55.731
I know, I know.

19:55.902 --> 19:58.132
You guys are like my family.

19:58.638 --> 20:00.833
Okay, okay, enough hugging.
Let's bolt.

20:01.007 --> 20:02.975
Yeah, let's get out of here.

20:03.309 --> 20:05.334
[WHIRRING]

20:08.181 --> 20:10.012
Relax, I was
just gonna cut some firewood.

20:11.117 --> 20:12.607
Would you all please leave?

20:15.588 --> 20:16.612
Hey, you may be a witch,

20:16.789 --> 20:21.021
but you don't impress me
with all your fairy dust, sparkly...

20:23.129 --> 20:24.926
Nice to have you back.

20:26.000 --> 20:27.524
It was terrible.

20:27.702 --> 20:29.033
Do you know how hard it is to shop

20:29.204 --> 20:32.401
for one sensible pump
in a size 11 wide?

20:32.574 --> 20:34.940
Not now, Salem.
I'm feeling miserable.

20:35.110 --> 20:36.805
[SNEEZES]

20:36.978 --> 20:39.071
Sabrina, we're just on our way...

20:39.247 --> 20:40.271
Are you sick?

20:40.448 --> 20:42.075
Yes, I am. Very.

20:42.250 --> 20:43.308
I'll make chicken soup.

20:43.485 --> 20:45.043
I'll get the thermometer.

20:45.220 --> 20:47.188
Wait, we're doing it again.

20:47.756 --> 20:49.155
Yeah, it's okay. Do it.

20:49.324 --> 20:51.622
Yep, we're being her aunts.

20:51.793 --> 20:54.660
- Be them.
- We'll see you later, Sabrina.

20:55.063 --> 20:58.328
No, but I'm feeling lousy here, guys.

20:58.500 --> 21:02.163
Auntie Morgan, Auntie Roxie?

21:02.337 --> 21:04.805
Anti-histamine.

